mainData.whatIsAsiHeading: What is the Artificial Superintelligence Alliance?

children.text: This token merger combines three premier projects from the blockchain space, creating an independent, open-source leader in the development of AGI. Token holders are expected to benefit as the project seeks to accelerate progress toward decentralized AGI, moving the world further toward the next step of Artificial Superintelligence.

teamMembers.name: Ben Goertzel
teamMembers.description: Dr. Ben Goertzel is a renowned leader in artificial intelligence, robotics, and computational finance with 25+ books and 150+ research papers published. With a Ph.D. in Mathematics and a career dedicated to both theoretical research and practical application of AI, Dr. Goertzel has been instrumental in advancing the field of artificial general intelligence (AGI). He is the leader of several prominent AI organizations, including SingularityNET, TrueAGI Inc., OpenCog Foundation, and the AGI Society, and was the Chief Scientist for notable AI companies such as Hanson Robotics. Dr. Goertzel's work has significantly contributed to the development of OpenCog Hyperon, an open-source AGI software project, and has played a crucial role in the creation of advanced robots like Sophia, Desdemona and Grace.
teamMembers.title: CEO and Chief Scientist of SingularityNET CEO of the Superintelligence Alliance

teamMembers.description: Humayun is an entrepreneur, investor, and tech visionary who is passionate about technologies such as AI, machine learning, autonomous agents, and blockchains. In the past, he was a founding investor in DeepMind, where he supported the commercialization of early-stage AI and deep neural network technology. Currently, he is leading Fetch.ai as CEO, a start-up building the autonomy of the future. He is also the chairman of the Artificial Superintelligence Alliance. Humayun is an expert on the topics of artificial intelligence, machine learning, autonomous agents, and the intersection of blockchain and commodities.
teamMembers.name: Humayun Sheikh
teamMembers.title: CEO of Fetch.ai and Chairman of the Artificial Superintelligence Alliance
Founder & CTO of Ocean Protocol, Board director in the Artificial Superintelligence Alliance Council
teamMembers.name: Trent McConaghy
teamMembers.description: Trent McConaghy has worked in AI since 1997, blockchain since 2013, and AI * blockchain since 2017. He worked on large-scale AI for semiconductors, via a PhD and two startups (both acquired). He worked on NFTs on Bitcoin (ascribe), decentralized databases (BigchainDB), and decentralized AI (Ocean Protocol). He published 40+ papers, 25+ patents, and two textbooks. He helped launch Token Engineering. He's given talks at the UN, Stanford, MIT, Berkeley, NASA, JPL, SFI, and more.

teamMembers.name: Bruce Pon
teamMembers.title: Founder & CEO of Ocean Protocol, Board director in the Artificial Superintelligence Alliance Council
teamMembers.description: Bruce Pon is the Founder of Ocean Protocol, a blockchain startup focused on bringing data and AI together since 2013. Previously, Bruce co-founded Avantalion, a consulting firm that helped to build 20 banks around the globe for companies such as Mercedes-Benz, Volkswagen, Mitsubishi & Jaguar LandRover. He has an Advanced Executive Certificate from MIT Sloan, a B.Sc in Engineering from the University of Saskatchewan, and has given guest lectures at Oxford, MIT Media Lab, Columbia University, and the European School of Management & Technology. In addition to being in the 2020 full-length documentary Cryptopia, Bruce was featured in Oxford University and Saïd Business School’s online Blockchain course as a guest expert and in ARTE’s The Digital Future.

teamMembers.title: COO of SingularityNET Board Director in the Superintelligence Alliance Council
teamMembers.name: Janet Adams
teamMembers.description: As the COO of SingularityNET, Janet Adams brings her extensive expertise and insights to the stage, captivating audiences with her deep understanding of disruptive technologies and their potential impact on various industries. With a passion for AI ethics and regulation, Janet's talks often revolve around the responsible and ethical use of AI in today's rapidly evolving world, alongside the positive potential of decentralised Artificial General Intelligence (AGI). Her dedication to a positive and beneficial Singularity for the benefit of humanity makes her an influential thought leader in the AI and blockchain industries.

mainData.oceanProtocolContent: Ocean Protocol was founded to level the playing field for AI and data. Its tools enable businesses and individuals to trade tokenized data assets seamlessly to manage data all along the AI model life cycle. Ocean-powered apps include enterprise-grade data exchanges, data science competitions, data DAOs, and Predictoor.

children.text: This merger seeks to accelerate progress toward decentralized AGI and further toward the next step of Artificial Superintelligence. This also leads to a single $ASI token with a combined utility of the three ecosystems.

mainData.aboutTheAlliance: The ASI Alliance represents a significant shift toward a decentralized AI ecosystem, offering an alternative to AI development dominated by big tech. By pooling their resources and expertise, Fetch.ai, SingularityNET, and Ocean Protocol aim to foster innovation, transparency, and inclusivity in the development of advanced AI technologies.
mainData.seoTitle: Artificial Superintelligence Alliance | The worlds largest open source, independent AI foundation.
mainData.singularityNetContent: SingularityNET was founded by Dr. Ben Goertzel with the mission of creating a decentralized, democratic, inclusive and beneficial Artificial General Intelligence (AGI). According to Dr. Goertzel, AGI should be independent of any central entity, open to anyone and not restricted to the narrow goals of a single corporation or a single country.
mainData.tokenMerge:
ASI combines the tokens of AGIX, OCEAN, and FET. With the three of the leading decentralized AI and Data solutions coming together under a single token, incentive and mission between the projects are aligned as progress is made towards a beneficial future.
